=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFPulse_ex7 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 100 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with evolving spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally rich.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: rich
  spectral_flux_normalized: evolving
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 100.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -3.4989
  harmonic_regularity: 0.2712
  pitch_clarity: 28.5578
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -19.0111
  resonance_freq: 1162.7930

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFPulse Example 7
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFPulse.html
// Tags: LFPulse, Classes, oscillator, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 7 ---
(
{
    [
        Pulse.ar(100, 0.3, 0.5),
        LFPulse.ar(100, 0, 0.3, 0.5)
    ] * 0.2
}.play
)
